The paper presents a deep reinforcement learning algorithm to solve the Select-MDP problem, which involves selecting a subset of items at each step. This problem is a combination of combinatorial optimization and reinforcement learning, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the large state and action spaces of the problem, which could indicate that it falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to address the state space explosion issue, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.RO (Robotics).
